textos_fuente.text: Staff - Golden Eagle Summer Sports Camp Email us: carly@goldeneaglecamp.org Call us: 415-519-6292 Visit us on social networks Home Our Program Our Program Schedule & Locations Staff FAQ Employment Opportunities Community Support Sign Up Parent Login Home Staff Our staff consists of highly qualified instructors and counselors with extensive background in their activities. MORE ABOUT US FAMILY OWNED AND OPERATED Golden Eagle Summer Sports Camp has been owned and operated by the Lodge Family since its founding in the summer of 1984. We are proud to serve our local community as one of the longest running family camps in the area. Together with Garrett and Kim Middleton, directors of our Homestead site, we have continued to grow in popularity each year. Our staff consists of hard working local high school and college students, dedicated to providing individualized attention to all campers to ensure they have the best summer ever. Most of our staff attended Golden Eagle as campers themselves and strive to provide campers the same joyful, fun filled summer camp experience they had. We hope you too will join the Golden Eagle family! OWNER & LOS ALTOS DIRECTOR STEFAAN LODGE Stefaan Lodge has been co-owner of Golden Eagle Summer Sports Camp and Director since 2002. He began attending the camp as a kindergartener in 1984 when it was started by his parents, Nelson and Monica Lodge. Through the years he attended camp as a camper and worked as a junior and senior counselor before taking over as owner and director. Stefaan was a three-sport varsity high school athlete and currently teaches at Los Altos High School. He has three young children, Carter (11), Kennedy (9), and Madison (7). He finds great joy in watching them spend their summers at Golden Eagle building the same lasting memories that he has carried with him over the past 4 decades. OPERATIONS CARLY LODGE Carly joined the Golden Eagle family when she and Stefaan met and began dating in 2008. To this day she claims she knew Stefaan was “the one“ when she visited camp, having only dated for a few months, and saw Stefaan’s amazing presence with the campers. Sure enough they were married in 2013 and together have 3 beautiful children. Carly manages the camp operations throughout the year and is responsible for the website and marketing efforts as well as handling all registrations, payments, community outreach and charitable contributions. HOMESTEAD DIRECTORS KIM & GARRETT MIDDLETION Garrett & Kim Middleton have been working with Golden Eagle Sports Camp for over two decades. Together they bring a wealth of knowledge about both athletics and childhood development and have watched their two boys, Drew and Griffin, thrive at the camp since they were young children, and are now helping to run the Homestead camp. Garrett has 2 decades of experience as a teacher, coach (basketball, softball, track & field, etc), and athletic director. Kim earned her Bachelor’s degree in Child Development and Liberal Studies. After she graduated, she worked as the Assistant Director at the Children’s Center of the Stanford Community for nine years and then went on to join the staff at Edgewood House School in Palo Alto for the next five years. During those years she was involved with Golden Eagle Sports Camp and now she enjoys being at the camp full time and working with all the campers to ensure they have an awesome camp experience. condition and is designed for all levels of play. Conveniently located only
minutes from downtown Rochester, Eagle Vale provides visitors with a golf,
dining and entertainment experience unlike any other in the area. Eagle Vale meticulously maintains its course to the highest standards and
features a computerized irrigation system, well maintained sand bunkers,
driving range, short game practice areas, and golf carts with canopies,
windshields, and golf bag protectors. Eagle Vale is a Certified Audubon Sanctuary Encompassed within the golf course are natural wetlands that provide nesting
areas for a variety of wildlife. There is an abundance of plant life and
flower gardens that enhance the natural beauty of the terrain. Eagle Vale
is proud to be the only golf course in western New York to have achieved the
prestigious distinction of being named a Certified Audubon Sanctuary by
Audubon International. From virtually every vantage point, sweeping views of Loch Raven Reservoir, towering trees and verdant golfing greens lend an air of majesty to the moment. And with each new experience, it becomes ever clearer that this is where you belong. Schedule A Tour Dawn Redwoods A Tale of Rare Beauty Our Club is home to about 75 dawn redwoods — one of the largest collections outside of China. Once prevalent throughout the Northern Hemisphere, these trees were thought to have become extinct until 1941, when a Chinese forester in the Sichuan province discovered more than 1,000 trees that had somehow survived. The trees at Eagle’s Nest are likely very close descendants of those discovered in China. How did so many of these magnificent trees find their way to Eagle’s Nest? According to Jimmy Watson, our first club president, his brother Bobby is to thank. “A nursery in York, PA, wanted to clear an area,” Jimmy explained. “So they said to Bobby, ‘Take ’em all … $1 apiece.’ They were the size of a broom handle. My brother and Roy Albin planted all the trees after work.” With that small investment roughly a half-century ago, another priceless attribute of Eagle’s Nest was born.
